Welcome to TailWind

installtion of tailwind
1-install node firstly
2-go to tailwind.css and get started and use postcss method
3- make a folder with tailwind name and open it in vs code -> go to terminal write npm init  ->  it iwll ask file name give tailwind _demo
4- description-Tailwind -> enter till last page 
5- install ----   npm i vite 
6- go to tailwind css or copy from below
  a- Install Tailwind CSS Install tailwindcss and its peer dependencies via npm, and create your tailwind.config.js file.
     npm install -D tailwindcss postcss autoprefixer
     npx tailwindcss init
  b- Add Tailwind to your PostCSS configuration Add tailwindcss and autoprefixer to your postcss.config.js file, or wherever PostCSS is configured in your project.

      module.exports = {
      plugins: {
      tailwindcss: {},
      autoprefixer: {},
    }
      }

c -Configure your template paths Add the paths to all of your template files in your tailwind.config.js file.
    /** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
  content: ["./src/**/*.{html,js}"],   //here maake content * to configure all files 
  theme: {
    extend: {},
  },
  plugins: [],
}

d- go to pakage.json and make start script using 
   "start"="vite"

e- make main.css and paste below script--Add the Tailwind directives to your CSS Add the @tailwind directives for each of Tailwindâ€™s layers to your main CSS file.
    @tailwind base;
    @tailwind components;
    @tailwind utilities;

f- make index.html and link main.css instead of style.css and do not go live just go to terminal and type
   npm start
  u will local address , hover on that and click -- ctrl+click it will open a document in browser 
  then come to vscode and in html body test your taliwind 

g- to quit app- ctrl+c
to start - npm start

make sure we have tailwind.cssand index.html in root folder 
